CatDescriptText: Monya Copeland, 1347 Bluff Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 2, 1957, pg. 2, with question: "Do you believe that one political party should be in control of all the offices in city, county, and state?" answer reads: "No, I don't think so. With a few of the opposition party in, there would be a more sever policy in checking and keeping things on an even keel."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Monya Copeland wearing light colored coat with high collar and single button at neck, earrings, and dark gloves, standing on sidewalk between building and car
